==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Necessitude
<hw>Ne*ces"si*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>necessitudo</ets>, fr. necesse. See <er>Necessray</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Necessitousness; want.</def> <rj><au>Sir M.
Hale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Necessary connection or relation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Between kings and their people, parents and their children, there
is so great a <qex>necessitude</qex>, propriety, and intercourse of
nature.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Necessity</ent>⟦br⟧
